&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s useful to know how many connections your web server can handle. It&amp;rsquo;s important to see how your server behaves under load. That&amp;rsquo;s why it&amp;rsquo;s necessary to benchmark it. We&amp;rsquo;ll see here how to benchmark it, and then we&amp;rsquo;ll look at some differences when using cache servers.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nginx Git and Gitweb</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Nginx_Git_et_Gitweb/</link><pubDate>Fri, 04 Jan 2013 17:28:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Nginx_Git_et_Gitweb/</guid><description>&lt;p>I spent a lot of time figuring out how to make Git over HTTP(S) and Gitweb coexist, but finally got it working.&lt;/p>

&lt;div class="alert alert-info d-flex" role="alert">
 &lt;div class="flex-shrink-1 alert-icon">
 
 &lt;span class="material-icons size-20 me-2">
 info
 &lt;/span>&lt;/div>
 
 &lt;div class="w-100">Consider using the &lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Gitweb_:_Installation_et_configuration_d'une_interface_web_pour_git/#Nginx">Gitweb&lt;/a> method only if you don&amp;rsquo;t need Git over HTTP(S)&lt;/div>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="configuration-method">Configuration Method &lt;a href="#configuration-method" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Here&amp;rsquo;s the method I used:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock linenos">
 &lt;pre id="fb53776" class="language-nginx line-numbers">
 &lt;code>server {
 listen 80;
 listen 443 ssl;

 ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/deimos.fr/server-unified.crt;
 ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/deimos.fr/server.key;
 ssl_session_timeout 5m;

 server_name git.deimos.fr;
 root /usr/share/gitweb/;

 access_log /var/log/nginx/git.deimos.fr_access.log;
 error_log /var/log/nginx/git.deimos.fr_error.log;

 index gitweb.cgi;

 # Drop config
 include drop.conf;

 # Git over https
 location /git/ {
 alias /var/cache/git/;
 if ($scheme = http) {
 rewrite ^ https://$host$request_uri permanent;
 }
 }

 # Gitweb
 location ~ gitweb\.cgi {
 fastcgi_cache mycache;
 fastcgi_cache_key $request_method$host$request_uri;
 fastcgi_cache_valid any 1h;
 include fastcgi_params;
 fastcgi_pass unix:/run/fcgiwrap.socket;
 }
}&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>With this configuration, Git over HTTPS is working (HTTP is redirected to HTTPS) and Gitweb is working too since everything matching gitweb.cgi is correctly routed.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>